  "prompt": "Is spot counselling for reserved candidates?",
  "response": "Whether or not spot counselling is available for reserved candidates depends on the specific policies of the institution or organization conducting the counselling. Generally, spot counselling is a process used to fill vacant seats that remain after the regular counselling rounds have been completed. It may be open to all candidates, including those from reserved categories, depending on institutional rules and regulatory guidelines. \n\nIt's important to check the specific details and notifications from the institution or organization offering the spot counselling to understand eligibility criteria, procedure, and whether reserved category candidates can participate.",
